- "Overall performance metrics" refers to the average micro F1 score, macro F1 score, and accuracy of each model; 
- "Most recent interaction details" include the timestamp and the username of the user who interacted with the model; 
- "Last updator roles" indicate whether the last update was made by an admin or a non-admin user; 
- "Updated within the last year" means the last update timestamp is within the past 365 days from the current date.
